race.comment: HAD IT ALL (8) resumed over 1200m at Beaumont-Newcastle 3 weeks ago, and after racing just off the pace, she fought on gamely to finish runner-up by 2 lengths. She has the winkers on for the first time, and with Keagan Latham keeping the faith, she looks well placed to go one better, especially with the aid of the pole position. OVERSHADOW (13) ran on late when making her debut, finishing a sound fifth over 1100m at Canterbury just over 3 weeks ago. She drops 3.5kg, and she should be tough to beat with that experience under her belt. LAPIS LAZULI (10) has been progressing nicely in both of her runs this prep, improving to finish third by half a length at Wyong over 1350m last time out. The blinkers are on for the first time, and she can test the top pick. Each way. BRUTAL ADVANCE (16) can't be faulted for his consistency, and did well to finish third at Moruya last start in a race where he should have finished even closer. Go again. DON'S PARTY (2) will be ready to rumble on debut.
